Introduction

Tiny-G was a four-member girl group formed by GNG Production. They officially debuted on August 23, 2012 with their first self-titled single "Tiny-G".

On February 10, 2015, GNG announced the group would go on an indefinite hiatus, with the members focusing on individual activities.

The group has presumably disbanded with the removal of their website and Mint leaving the group in 2016 to become a solo artist.
